               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl1240-1">Peeters, Martyrologe , 155, 187. DHGE, XVI, 1967, col. 791-93 (R. Aubert) . Fiey, Nisibe, 20-21. BS, V, 508- 509 (J .-M. Sauget). Trad. anglaise dans Brock-Harvey, Holy Women, 152- 76.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Febronia of Nisibis was a martyr and nun who lived in a convent near Nisibis. She was renown for her beauty, learning, asceticism, and bravery. She was martyred for refusing to marry a pagan statesman. She is venerated in the Syriac, Latin, and Greek traditions.</note>
